history.content: 162 is a HUGE project course by itself. 186 is also high workload when homeworks are released. You said that you’re also interning part time 20 hrs/week, and honestly I don’t think taking both 162 and 186 is a good idea (unless you just want to pass the course). Additionally, 162 is worked on with a group and it might not be fair for your group mates if you don’t have as much time as them to contribute to the projects and meet up regularly. I recommend you should take 186 and maybe a light workload CS course if you need another tech

How many estimated hours per week would just 162 + 186 take for the average student? I'm planning on interning part-time (20 hours/week) during the Fall, and would like to know if it would be feasible to take just 162 and 186 (I plan to get 4 additional filler units from somewhere that require minimal time/effort to pass) whilst doing so. I also don't intend to spend any time on any other commitments besides recruitment/interview prep. Thanks!
